<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES43-5 AND ES53-5 -
        DISASSEMBLY - MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="14">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300938">Figure 36</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300938" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300936" filename="../figg13/g1300936.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Mainshaft Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. INPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. INPUT BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. OIL RING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. MAINSHAFT POCKET BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>6. CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>7. 4TH AND 5TH SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>9. MAINSHAFT 4TH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>10. THRUSTWASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>11. MAINSHAFT 3RD GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>12. 2ND AND 3RD SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>13. MAINSHAFT 2ND GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>14. REVERSE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>15. 1ST AND REVERSE CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>16. THRUSTWASHER LOCK PINS</callout1>
                <callout1>17. MAINSHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>18. MAINSHAFT 1ST GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>19. SPEEDOMETER DRIVE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>20. FLANGE/YOKE</callout1>
                <callout1>21. WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>22. NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>23. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                <callout1>24. COUNTERSHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>25. COUNTERSHAFT 2ND GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>26. SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>27. COUNTERSHAFT 3RD GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>28. COUNTERSHAFT 4TH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>29. COUNTERSHAFT DRIVE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>30. REVERSE IDLER GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>31. REVERSE IDLER SHAFT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft subassembly on a bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300939">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300939" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300937" filename="../figg13/g1300937.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Place Mainshaft Subassembly on Bench</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wearing safety glasses, remove the spiral snap ring from the groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300940">Figure 38</hotlnk>). The easiest way to do this is to place a screwdriver
                under one end and work it around the snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300940" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300938" filename="../figg13/g1300938.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Spiral Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to prevent possible personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next attach a puller to the 4th-5th speed clutch gear. Remove the pocket bearing, spiral
                snap ring, and clutch gear together (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300941">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300941" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300939" filename="../figg13/g1300939.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Remove Pocket Bearing, Spiral Snap Ring, and Clutch Gear Together</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4th speed gear and caged needle bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300942">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300942" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300940" filename="../figg13/g1300940.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Remove 4th Speed Gear and Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next remove the snap ring, thrust washer, lock pin, 3rd speed gear, and caged needle bearing
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300943">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300943" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300941" filename="../figg13/g1300941.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Remove 3rd Speed Gear and Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300944">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300944" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300942" filename="../figg13/g1300942.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Remove 2nd-3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring and 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300945">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300945" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300943" filename="../figg13/g1300943.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Remove Snap Ring and 2nd-3rd Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd speed gear and the caged needle bearing from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300946">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300946" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300944" filename="../figg13/g1300944.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Remove 2nd Speed Gear and Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, thrust washer, lock pin, 1st speed gear, and the caged needle bearings
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300947">Figure 45</hotlnk>). Remember to wear safety glasses during service.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300947" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300945" filename="../figg13/g1300945.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Remove 1st Speed Gear and Caged Needle Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The mainshaft uses caged needle bearings under all gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300948">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300948" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300946" filename="../figg13/g1300946.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Mainshaft Uses Caged Needle Bearings Under All Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The clutch gears-not the mainshaft- contain the gear locks. The only exception to this is
                the 1st-reverse mainshaft clutch gear which contains gear locks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300949">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300949" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300947" filename="../figg13/g1300947.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. 1st-Reverse Mainshaft Clutch Gear Contains Gear Locks</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The synchronizers have separate clutching rings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300950">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300950" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300948" filename="../figg13/g1300948.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Synchronizers Have Separate Clutching Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The brass synchronizer outer race diameters are coated with GYLON&#174; friction material
                for smoother shifting (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300951">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300951" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300949" filename="../figg13/g1300949.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Brass Synchronizer Outer Race Diameters Are Coated With Friction Material</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
